[owl hooting]

3
00:00:32.541 --> 00:00:33.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't look at those.

4
00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:37.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sumi.

5
00:00:39.791 --> 00:00:40.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Taka.

6
00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:45.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hm. I'm just getting used
to saying names again.

7
00:00:46.166 --> 00:00:48.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long have you been here
on your own?

8
00:00:48.791 --> 00:00:50.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, years.

9
00:00:50.875 --> 00:00:53.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or possibly a couple of months.

10
00:00:55.791 --> 00:00:57.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So...

11
00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:00.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you've seen the parlous condition
of my new home.

12
00:01:00.750 --> 00:01:03.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It wasn't what we expected.

13
00:01:03.500 --> 00:01:06.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well... there was a small battle.

14
00:01:06.833 --> 00:01:09.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It must have been
a legendary battle.

15
00:01:10.166 --> 00:01:12.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mostly just desperate and sad.

16
00:01:14.541 --> 00:01:17.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What exactly happened to the mechanism
that moves the castle?

17
00:01:19.125 --> 00:01:20.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She melted it.

18
00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:26.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[inhales, exhales]

19
00:01:26.166 --> 00:01:27.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never mind.

20
00:01:28.916 --> 00:01:32.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So you were part of the court
of this vampire you call Cho?

21
00:01:32.500 --> 00:01:35.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. In northern Japan.

22
00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Far from anywhere.

23
00:01:37.791 --> 00:01:40.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Sumi]
<i>We all lived in her secret fortress.</i>

24
00:01:40.875 --> 00:01:43.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Trapped in her fortress.</i>

25
00:01:44.291 --> 00:01:47.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Taka]<i> We were given</i>
<i>to Cho's hidden court as children.</i>

26
00:01:48.625 --> 00:01:52.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It amused her to have</i>
<i>a human honor guard.</i>

27
00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:55.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Not that she needed guarding.</i>

28
00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:57.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sometimes,</i>

29
00:01:57.166 --> 00:01:59.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>it was her pleasure</i>
<i>to have us allow a hunter</i>

30
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:03.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to pass through her ranks</i>
<i>and into the court.</i>

31
00:02:07.041 --> 00:02:09.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Sumi]
<i>This was how it was... every day.</i>

32
00:02:11.166 --> 00:02:12.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Some new horror.</i>

33
00:02:13.041 --> 00:02:14.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Some new punishment.</i>

34
00:02:15.666 --> 00:02:19.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Some new boastful exercise</i>
<i>of her complete power over us.</i>

35
00:02:32.375 --> 00:02:34.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Every day was slavery.</i>

36
00:02:35.500 --> 00:02:37.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Every day was death.</i>

37
00:02:38.416 --> 00:02:40.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[swords clanging]

38
00:02:40.833 --> 00:02:42.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And we had to watch it all.</i>

39
00:03:00.125 --> 00:03:03.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Taka]
<i>Cho was ancient and arrogant.</i>

40
00:03:03.458 --> 00:03:06.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>She had lived forever</i>
<i>where no army could reach her.</i>

41
00:03:06.791 --> 00:03:09.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No superior power could end her.</i>

42
00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:11.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We just watched.</i>

43
00:03:12.333 --> 00:03:13.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And learned.</i>

44
00:03:20.791 --> 00:03:23.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Sumi]
<i>We spent years studying how she lived...</i>

45
00:03:23.916 --> 00:03:25.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>studying how she fought.</i>

46
00:03:26.041 --> 00:03:28.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>We learned from her every victory.</i>

47
00:03:28.250 --> 00:03:30.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Memorized her every weakness.</i>

48
00:03:38.958 --> 00:03:43.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Our lives became nothing</i>
<i>but the development of plans to end her.</i>

49
00:04:14.875 --> 00:04:16.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Taka]
<i>We read her books</i>

50
00:04:16.708 --> 00:04:18.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and listened to her legend</i>

51
00:04:18.541 --> 00:04:22.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and wished only for the chance</i>
<i>to free our people from her teeth.</i>

52
00:04:37.166 --> 00:04:39.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And then she left.</i>

53
00:04:39.166 --> 00:04:41.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Summoned to Dracula's war court.</i>

54
00:04:42.125 --> 00:04:43.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[bow twangs]

55
00:04:59.375 --> 00:05:01.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Sumi]
<i>We killed all her guards</i>

56
00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:04.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and freed the people</i>
<i>of the hidden court within days.</i>

57
00:05:05.833 --> 00:05:08.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But Cho was always</i>
<i>going to come back.</i>

58
00:05:10.666 --> 00:05:13.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So we left to hunt her.</i>

59
00:05:13.125 --> 00:05:15.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Because if she returns to the court,

60
00:05:15.791 --> 00:05:17.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it will begin all over again.

61
00:05:18.458 --> 00:05:20.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If she's truly dead,

62
00:05:20.166 --> 00:05:23.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
then other vampires will
eventually take her court over.

63
00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And our freedom
will mean nothing.

64
00:05:29.416 --> 00:05:32.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need a friend, Alucard.

65
00:05:38.250 --> 00:05:39.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You need instruction.

66
00:05:40.375 --> 00:05:42.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Perhaps one
or two new weapons.

67
00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:46.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe learn a little magic?

68
00:05:47.208 --> 00:05:48.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Magic?

69
00:05:49.625 --> 00:05:52.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Really?
-Magic.

70
00:05:53.208 --> 00:05:54.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do we think?

71
00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:05.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps]

72
00:06:08.750 --> 00:06:10.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Morana sighs]

73
00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:13.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So...
what do we think?

74
00:06:14.791 --> 00:06:16.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Striga]
It's always the same.

75
00:06:17.250 --> 00:06:19.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Carmilla always has a scheme.

76
00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:21.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's a dreamer, Striga.

77
00:06:22.875 --> 00:06:24.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

78
00:06:24.291 --> 00:06:28.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's never, "Gather round, girls.
I have a dream to tell you about."

79
00:06:28.125 --> 00:06:30.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's arms waving in the air

80
00:06:30.416 --> 00:06:33.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and "Vampires and sisters,
I have a scheme!"

81
00:06:33.125 --> 00:06:35.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

82
00:06:35.791 --> 00:06:37.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Ah.
-Tell me I'm wrong.

83
00:06:40.625 --> 00:06:42.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, you're not wrong.

84
00:06:42.791 --> 00:06:44.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But she did get us here.

85
00:06:45.083 --> 00:06:49.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's because of Carmilla that we got
to fall in love in a fairy-tale castle.

86
00:06:49.625 --> 00:06:51.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, God, Morana.

87
00:06:51.541 --> 00:06:53.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You sound like Lenore.

88
00:06:53.291 --> 00:06:55.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is it still romantic
if I'm sick on your hair?

89
00:06:55.958 --> 00:06:58.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughs] Oh, shut up.

90
00:06:58.708 --> 00:07:01.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's been amazing,
and you know it.

91
00:07:02.250 --> 00:07:04.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes. I admit it, all right?

92
00:07:04.916 --> 00:07:06.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's been amazing.

93
00:07:07.250 --> 00:07:10.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I also remember
how hard it was to get here.

94
00:07:10.875 --> 00:07:14.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You and Carmilla only see
the present and the future.

95
00:07:14.375 --> 00:07:16.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can't shake the past.

96
00:07:16.916 --> 00:07:18.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Neither can Carmilla.

97
00:07:19.625 --> 00:07:21.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She still has nightmares
about the years

98
00:07:21.625 --> 00:07:23.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
before she killed the vampire
who turned her.

99
00:07:23.916 --> 00:07:28.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She doesn't forget, Striga.
She just looks ahead.

100
00:07:28.666 --> 00:07:33.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But taking and controlling
an 800-mile-wide corridor of land...

101
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:35.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Morana]
It's big.

102
00:07:35.791 --> 00:07:37.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Striga]
Big scheme.

103
00:07:37.333 --> 00:07:38.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Morana]
Big<i> dream.</i>

104
00:07:41.541 --> 00:07:43.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fucking scheme.

105
00:07:43.208 --> 00:07:46.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is what she does,
she pulls this stuff out of the air

106
00:07:46.250 --> 00:07:49.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and expects the three of us
to make it happen.

107
00:07:50.291 --> 00:07:53.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But can it be done?
Militarily?

108
00:07:54.041 --> 00:07:55.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ahh. Pfft!

109
00:07:58.125 --> 00:07:59.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In theory?

110
00:08:00.166 --> 00:08:02.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I need more intelligence
from the territory.

111
00:08:03.166 --> 00:08:06.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But in theory?
You said it'd be hard to police.

112
00:08:06.500 --> 00:08:10.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I mean, would we have to throw
a stockade around the corridor, or...?

113
00:08:10.208 --> 00:08:11.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, no.

114
00:08:12.041 --> 00:08:14.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The border would be entirely notional.

115
00:08:14.666 --> 00:08:18.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a question of putting
rotating sweeper patrols on the border,

116
00:08:18.583 --> 00:08:20.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
building watchtowers,
taking towns,

117
00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:23.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and forming fortified camps
to concentrate the humans in.

118
00:08:24.625 --> 00:08:26.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So you know you can do it.

119
00:08:26.791 --> 00:08:29.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, maybe.

120
00:08:29.708 --> 00:08:30.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Possibly.

121
00:08:31.666 --> 00:08:33.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But it would be hard.

122
00:08:33.416 --> 00:08:36.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything worth doing is hard.

123
00:08:36.250 --> 00:08:39.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And just think: if we did this,

124
00:08:39.916 --> 00:08:43.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you would be commanding
the army of an empire.

125
00:08:43.916 --> 00:08:45.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

126
00:08:45.083 --> 00:08:49.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We would own and control the land
from here to Braila.

127
00:08:49.416 --> 00:08:51.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Almost to the Black Sea.

128
00:08:51.166 --> 00:08:53.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not a country or a region, love.

129
00:08:53.916 --> 00:08:55.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's an empire!

130
00:08:55.666 --> 00:08:58.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
An imperial army.

131
00:08:58.541 --> 00:09:02.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Applying all the lessons
from empires of old.

132
00:09:02.541 --> 00:09:07.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you can win the war,
I can perfect the machinery of empire.

133
00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:09.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

134
00:09:12.166 --> 00:09:13.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is how she does it.

135
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:16.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The horrible bitch gets in our heads

136
00:09:16.333 --> 00:09:19.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and inspires us to make
her madness work.

137
00:09:19.541 --> 00:09:21.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, it is.

138
00:09:21.916 --> 00:09:24.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But imagine. Hm?

139
00:09:24.291 --> 00:09:25.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Imagine.

140
00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:30.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
An empire ruled by four women.

141
00:09:31.875 --> 00:09:34.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Vampires and sisters.

142
00:09:38.625 --> 00:09:40.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[both] Vampires and sisters,

143
00:09:40.916 --> 00:09:43.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
we have a scheme!

144
00:09:43.125 --> 00:09:45.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[both laughing]

145
00:09:52.125 --> 00:09:54.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[crows cawing]

146
00:10:06.458 --> 00:10:08.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They may be crazy,
but they're careful.

147
00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:11.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[cawing continues]

148
00:10:24.041 --> 00:10:26.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Time to play the game.

149
00:10:26.375 --> 00:10:28.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Be masterly, young man.

150
00:10:40.041 --> 00:10:41.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Saint Germain]
Prior Sala!

151
00:10:41.833 --> 00:10:43.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thank you again
for this opportunity

152
00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:47.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and this insight into
your fascinating new philosophy.

153
00:10:47.541 --> 00:10:51.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wish you'd stop talking to me
like I'm insane,

154
00:10:51.458 --> 00:10:53.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Saint Germain.

155
00:10:53.166 --> 00:10:56.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not like I am
some demented child

156
00:10:56.416 --> 00:10:58.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that will wet itself

157
00:10:58.458 --> 00:11:01.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
if you stop
patting me on the head.

158
00:11:01.666 --> 00:11:05.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[stammers]
Oh, well, um, I'm... sorry?

159
00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:08.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't be sorry.

160
00:11:08.833 --> 00:11:11.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just be better.

161
00:11:11.291 --> 00:11:14.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes. Of course.
Um... thank you.

162
00:11:18.875 --> 00:11:21.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lovely... place.

163
00:11:22.500 --> 00:11:24.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[soft creaking]

164
00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:40.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[coughs]
Quite lovely.

165
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:42.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This suffices.

166
00:11:50.041 --> 00:11:54.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is part of the library.
You can start here.

167
00:11:55.291 --> 00:11:58.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very original shelving method.

168
00:11:58.666 --> 00:12:00.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, well...

169
00:12:00.166 --> 00:12:05.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the grand scheme of things,
they no longer seemed necessary.

170
00:12:05.166 --> 00:12:07.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you persuaded me

171
00:12:07.250 --> 00:12:11.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that there may yet be
something of worth in them.

172
00:12:11.166 --> 00:12:13.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So... have at it.

173
00:12:20.916 --> 00:12:25.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Might I point out that
your wall hanging is crooked?

174
00:12:25.791 --> 00:12:29.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It got knocked askew
when our visitor arrived.

175
00:12:29.416 --> 00:12:32.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's not something we give
too much thought to.

176
00:12:32.541 --> 00:12:36.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He may even be pointing
in the right direction now.

177
00:12:37.166 --> 00:12:38.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Towards Hell.

178
00:12:38.541 --> 00:12:41.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Where the night creature came from.
Your "visitor."

179
00:12:43.041 --> 00:12:47.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why do we call them
"night creatures,"

180
00:12:47.375 --> 00:12:48.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Saint Germain?

181
00:12:51.125 --> 00:12:52.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, because...

182
00:12:53.791 --> 00:12:55.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
they only come at night, I suppose.

183
00:12:55.875 --> 00:13:00.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Or it's a simple translation
of a very long Prussian word.

184
00:13:00.125 --> 00:13:02.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But they bring light.

185
00:13:02.208 --> 00:13:06.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The very name Lucifer
means "light-bringer."

186
00:13:07.916 --> 00:13:11.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you stopped
believing in God, Prior?

187
00:13:12.125 --> 00:13:13.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not at all.

188
00:13:13.666 --> 00:13:16.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
God created everything.

189
00:13:16.875 --> 00:13:19.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
God created Hell.

190
00:13:19.208 --> 00:13:21.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If God is perfect,

191
00:13:21.166 --> 00:13:24.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
then causing Lucifer
to go to Hell is his plan.

192
00:13:25.833 --> 00:13:29.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The wisdom of Hell
and its night creatures

193
00:13:29.541 --> 00:13:32.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
is God's wisdom.

194
00:13:33.250 --> 00:13:37.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't you see how it all
begins to make a terrible sense?

195
00:13:38.541 --> 00:13:40.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It is indeed fascinating.

196
00:13:40.750 --> 00:13:42.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tell me...

197
00:13:42.375 --> 00:13:46.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
how did you arrive at that symbol
to identify yourselves?

198
00:13:47.041 --> 00:13:48.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This?

199
00:13:48.416 --> 00:13:52.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those of us who bore witness
to the visitor wear it

200
00:13:52.791 --> 00:13:55.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
because he gave it to us.

201
00:13:55.875 --> 00:13:57.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you know what it means?

202
00:13:57.958 --> 00:14:01.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It is his mark.
-No, Sala.

203
00:14:01.625 --> 00:14:04.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's the alchemical sign
for sulphur.

204
00:14:05.125 --> 00:14:08.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Used by philosophers to denote Hell.

205
00:14:10.250 --> 00:14:13.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We wear the mark of Hell?

206
00:14:13.125 --> 00:14:14.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

207
00:14:15.458 --> 00:14:17.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Magnificent!

208
00:14:21.625 --> 00:14:23.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Indeed.

209
00:14:23.375 --> 00:14:26.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You are a wise man,
Saint Germain.

210
00:14:26.916 --> 00:14:29.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I confess I had doubts about you.

211
00:14:29.625 --> 00:14:34.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I stand delighted that
you would bring us your knowledge.

212
00:14:34.375 --> 00:14:36.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please! Begin!

213
00:14:37.458 --> 00:14:38.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Find us more treasure

214
00:14:38.916 --> 00:14:43.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that we may increase our knowledge
of the true way of things.

215
00:14:44.125 --> 00:14:47.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You will be brought
bread and wine shortly.

216
00:14:52.750 --> 00:14:54.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But please...

217
00:14:54.333 --> 00:14:58.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
restrict yourself to
this hall for the moment.

218
00:14:58.666 --> 00:15:01.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Much work goes on elsewhere,

219
00:15:01.333 --> 00:15:04.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I would not have it disturbed.

220
00:15:04.666 --> 00:15:06.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Yes?
-Yes.

221
00:15:06.625 --> 00:15:09.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course. This hall only...
for the moment.

222
00:15:09.916 --> 00:15:11.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excellent.

223
00:15:16.666 --> 00:15:18.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

224
00:15:44.166 --> 00:15:46.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are we doing?

225
00:15:46.125 --> 00:15:48.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We are gathering information.

226
00:15:48.416 --> 00:15:50.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Understanding the territory.

227
00:15:51.041 --> 00:15:53.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You sound like a burglar.

228
00:15:53.125 --> 00:15:55.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm a drifter, Sypha.

229
00:15:55.291 --> 00:15:58.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't roll up in
a cute little wagon

230
00:15:58.166 --> 00:16:01.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in my quaint speaker robes
and get alms from the locals.

231
00:16:01.583 --> 00:16:03.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Course I've been a burglar.

232
00:16:03.166 --> 00:16:05.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We could just ask people
some questions.

233
00:16:05.750 --> 00:16:06.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[scarred monk]
Hey.

234
00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:12.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, good.

235
00:16:12.916 --> 00:16:15.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, good! Hello!

236
00:16:15.416 --> 00:16:16.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Move away.

237
00:16:16.875 --> 00:16:17.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Gladly!

238
00:16:18.041 --> 00:16:20.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just have
a few questions for you.

239
00:16:21.666 --> 00:16:24.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nobody comes near our home. Move.

240
00:16:25.666 --> 00:16:27.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Calm down.

241
00:16:32.375 --> 00:16:33.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sypha clears throat]

242
00:16:33.666 --> 00:16:36.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We are visitors
to your lovely town.

243
00:16:36.750 --> 00:16:39.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There was only one... Visitor.

244
00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:43.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
OK... we are travelers,

245
00:16:43.625 --> 00:16:45.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
pausing here for a few days.

246
00:16:45.916 --> 00:16:48.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And my idiot servant here, and I,

247
00:16:48.625 --> 00:16:52.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
couldn't help but notice
your pretty priory...

248
00:16:52.250 --> 00:16:53.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and...

249
00:16:55.166 --> 00:16:56.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
your armband.

250
00:16:57.500 --> 00:16:59.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hadn't gotten
a close look at that before.

251
00:16:59.875 --> 00:17:02.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enough. Move away.

252
00:17:02.875 --> 00:17:05.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We protect this place.

253
00:17:05.750 --> 00:17:07.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
From what?

254
00:17:07.375 --> 00:17:09.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Prying eyes.

255
00:17:09.083 --> 00:17:10.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anyone who tries to interfere.

256
00:17:10.666 --> 00:17:13.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Anyone who gets
in the way of the work.

257
00:17:13.291 --> 00:17:16.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Sypha] Do you know
what the sign on your arm is?

258
00:17:16.166 --> 00:17:18.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[scarred monk]
The Visitor gave it to us.

259
00:17:19.041 --> 00:17:22.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's the work?
What are you doing in there?

260
00:17:23.041 --> 00:17:24.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No more.

261
00:17:25.208 --> 00:17:27.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're new here.

262
00:17:27.166 --> 00:17:29.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So, in the interests of a quiet life,

263
00:17:30.041 --> 00:17:32.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll give you this one chance.

264
00:17:32.333 --> 00:17:35.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Everyone here knows
not to approach the priory.

265
00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:39.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Everyone here knows
not to ask questions.

266
00:17:39.250 --> 00:17:41.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You leave us alone.

267
00:17:41.666 --> 00:17:43.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have work to do.

268
00:17:43.875 --> 00:17:45.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fine.

269
00:17:45.291 --> 00:17:48.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Thank you<i> very </i>much
for your kindness.

270
00:17:52.500 --> 00:17:54.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have your whip ready.

271
00:17:54.166 --> 00:17:55.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Just one more thing.

272
00:17:56.958 --> 00:17:59.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Speakers tend to be
natural prey in towns,

273
00:17:59.291 --> 00:18:01.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
because we don't carry weapons.

274
00:18:01.166 --> 00:18:04.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So we all learn how to spot
when someone's concealing a knife.

275
00:18:05.791 --> 00:18:08.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't you think monks
wearing a magic sign for Hell

276
00:18:08.875 --> 00:18:12.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and hiding blades in their robes
is a little obvious...

277
00:18:12.375 --> 00:18:13.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
even for a small town?

278
00:18:17.625 --> 00:18:19.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see you.

279
00:18:25.625 --> 00:18:27.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sypha sighs] Priests with knives.

280
00:18:27.916 --> 00:18:29.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is Gresit all over again.

281
00:18:29.791 --> 00:18:31.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Trevor] Are you sure
you didn't overplay it?

282
00:18:31.375 --> 00:18:33.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I mean, you do have a... habit of... uh--

283
00:18:34.750 --> 00:18:36.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps.

284
00:18:36.333 --> 00:18:39.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But quietly confident people
are competent and careful.

285
00:18:39.583 --> 00:18:41.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nervous people make mistakes.

286
00:18:41.916 --> 00:18:45.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd rather they were nervous
than happy in their work.

287
00:18:50.250 --> 00:18:52.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I thought just rolling up
to the front door

288
00:18:52.416 --> 00:18:55.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and annoying some mad monks
would do the trick...

289
00:18:55.250 --> 00:18:57.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would have done it
my fucking self.

290
00:18:58.291 --> 00:19:00.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That place stinks of magic.

291
00:19:00.541 --> 00:19:03.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're doing something terrible inside.

292
00:19:03.791 --> 00:19:04.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gulps]

293
00:19:06.416 --> 00:19:08.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps]

294
00:19:24.708 --> 00:19:26.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[footsteps continue]

295
00:19:40.291 --> 00:19:41.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have one question.

296
00:19:42.625 --> 00:19:44.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, for God's sake.

297
00:19:44.416 --> 00:19:47.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm only alive because
Carmilla wants a forgemaster, aren't I?

298
00:19:47.791 --> 00:19:50.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Stop pretending that this is anything
other than what it is.

299
00:19:51.875 --> 00:19:53.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll answer your question.

300
00:19:54.166 --> 00:19:59.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, Carmilla<i> is </i>keeping you around
because she'd like a forgemaster.

301
00:20:00.625 --> 00:20:02.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now<i> you </i>answer<i> my </i>question.

302
00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:07.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not poisoned.

303
00:20:17.500 --> 00:20:18.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

304
00:20:19.291 --> 00:20:20.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good.

