322
00:21:11.875 --> 00:21:14.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is exactly<i> our </i>plan.

323
00:21:15.041 --> 00:21:17.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So he lied to you?

324
00:21:18.541 --> 00:21:19.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

325
00:21:20.041 --> 00:21:23.666 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He... He withheld.

326
00:21:23.791 --> 00:21:26.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh. Well, never mind.

327
00:21:26.125 --> 00:21:27.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was he going to give you

328
00:21:27.708 --> 00:21:30.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for doing this work
that he lied to you about?

329
00:21:30.666 --> 00:21:34.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What was your reward for serving
a man who lied about his intents?

330
00:21:35.125 --> 00:21:36.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ach.

331
00:21:36.458 --> 00:21:39.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I-I assumed I would live outside
whatever enclosures

332
00:21:39.666 --> 00:21:42.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
were placed around
the remaining humans.

333
00:21:42.625 --> 00:21:44.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You "assumed."

334
00:21:44.250 --> 00:21:47.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not sure there was ever
a conversation, as such.

335
00:21:47.541 --> 00:21:50.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He would have continued
to need night creatures.

336
